It gets weirder. When I remove the second parameter ("x"), it compiles fine.

{code}
object Control {
  def repeat[T](count: Int = 1)(thunk: => T) : T = (0 until count).map(_ => thunk).last
  def repeat[T](thunk: => T) : T = repeat()(thunk)

  repeat(3.14)
  repeat(count=5)(3.14)
}
{code}

No error with scalac now.
